# Lower case, special characters replacement and ponctuation and white space elimination
import re
import unicodedata
def preproc(message):
    #print message
    message = str(message)
    message = message.lower()
    message = unicode(message, "utf-8")
    message = unicodedata.normalize("NFKD", message).encode('ascii', 'ignore').lower().replace(' ', '-')
    message = re.sub("[^a-zA-Z]", " ", message) 
    message = re.sub(" +", " ", message) 
    return message

#Putting a "SUBJECT_" prefix to each word in the text
def append_subj(text):
    new_text = []
    for word in text.split():
        new_text.append("SUBJECT_" + word)
    return " ".join(new_text)
        
#Cleaning message and subject
emails["clean_message"] = emails["mensagem"].apply(preproc)
emails["clean_subject"] = emails["assunto"].apply(preproc)

#Applying SUBJECT_ append
emails["clean_subject"] = emails["clean_subject"].apply(lambda x : append_subj(x))

#Concatenate subject to message    
emails["clean_message"] = emails.apply(lambda x : str(x["clean_subject"]) + " " + str(x["clean_message"]), axis=1) 

#print example
print emails["clean_message"][n_example]

Model Evaluation Metrics¶

  • Global Accuracy
  • Confusion Matrix
  • Leave One Out
    • Accuracy, Precision and Recall
  • Complete Report
    • Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1-Score, Confusion Matrix and ROC

Global Accuracy: number of examples with all labels predicted Confusion Matrix: True N P Pred N [ TN , FN ] P [ FP, TP ]

from sklearn.metrics import hamming_loss

from sklearn.cross_validation import cross_val_score, LeaveOneOut, KFold
from scipy.stats import sem
from sklearn import metrics

def evaluate_cross_validation(clf, X, y, K):
    cv = KFold(len(y), K, shuffle=True, random_state=0)
    # by default the score used is the one returned by score >>>
    scores = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, cv=cv)
    precisions = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, scoring='precision', cv=cv)
    recalls = cross_val_score(clf, X, y, scoring='recall', cv=cv)
    #print scores
    #print precisions
    print ("Mean score: {0:.3f} (+/-{1:.3f})").format(np.mean(scores), sem(scores))
    print ("Mean precision: {0:.3f} (+/-{1:.3f})").format(np.mean(precisions), sem(precisions))
    print ("Mean recall: {0:.3f} (+/-{1:.3f})").format(np.mean(recalls), sem(recalls))
    return np.mean(scores)

def global_accuracy(y_pred, y_true):
    globally_right = 0
    for point in range(y_true.shape[0]):
        no_miss_class = True
        for label in range(y_true.shape[1]):
            if y_pred.loc[y_true.index[point], str(emails.columns.values[label+3])] != y_true.loc[y_true.index[point],str(emails.columns.values[label+3])]:                              
                no_miss_class = False  
        if no_miss_class:
            globally_right += 1
    return globally_right / float(y_pred.shape[0])

def confusion_matrix_for_classes(y_pred, y_true):
    for label in range(y_true.shape[1]):
        conf_matrix_one_class(y_pred, y_true, str(emails.columns.values[label+3]))

def conf_matrix_one_class(y_pred, y_true, label):
    print "---------------------------------"
    print "Confusion matrix for", label
    print "Positive predictions: ", y_pred[label].sum()
    print confusion_matrix(y_pred[label], y_true[label]) 
    print "---------------------------------"

def loo_cv(X_train, y_train, clf):
    #y_train = y_train.ix[:, 1].as_matrix()
    y_train = y_train.as_matrix()
    loo = LeaveOneOut(X_train.shape[0])
    scores = np.zeros(X_train.shape[0])
    precisions = np.zeros(X_train.shape[0])
    recalls = np.zeros(X_train.shape[0])
    for train_index, test_index in loo:
        X_train_cv, X_test_cv = X_train[train_index], X_train[test_index]
        y_train_cv, y_test_cv = y_train[train_index], y_train[test_index]
        clf = clf.fit(X_train_cv,y_train_cv)
        y_pred = clf.predict(X_test_cv)
        scores[test_index] = metrics.accuracy_score(y_test_cv.astype(int), y_pred.astype(int))
        precisions[test_index] = metrics.precision_score(y_test_cv.astype(int), y_pred.astype(int))
        recalls[test_index] = metrics.recall_score(y_test_cv.astype(int), y_pred.astype(int))
    print ("Accuracy: {0:.3f} (+/-{1:.3f})").format(np.mean(scores), sem(scores))
    print ("Precision: {0:.3f} (+/-{1:.3f})").format(np.mean(precisions), sem(precisions))
    print ("Recall: {0:.3f} (+/-{1:.3f})").format(np.mean(recalls), sem(recalls))

def complete_report(y_pred, y_test):
    print "Global Accuracy: ", global_accuracy(y_pred, y_test)
    for i in range(n_classes):
        label = str(emails.columns.values[i+3])
        print "*********************************"
        print label + ": "
        print "Accuracy: %.2f" \
        % float((y_pred[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])] == y_test[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])]).sum() / float(y_test.shape[0]))
        print "Precision: ", metrics.precision_score(y_test[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])].astype(int), y_pred[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])].astype(int))
        print "Recall: ", metrics.recall_score(y_test[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])].astype(int), y_pred[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])].astype(int))
        print "F1-Score: ", metrics.f1_score(y_test[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])].astype(int), y_pred[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])].astype(int))
        conf_matrix_one_class(y_pred, y_test, str(emails.columns.values[i+3]))
        try: 
            print "Roc Area: ", metrics.roc_auc_score(y_test[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])].astype(int), y_pred[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])].astype(int))
            roc_curve_label(y_pred[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])], y_test[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])])

def roc_curve_label(y_pred, y_test):
    fpr, tpr, _ = metrics.roc_curve(y_test, y_pred)
    plt.figure(1)
    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')
    plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label='RT + LR')
    plt.xlabel('False positive rate')
    plt.ylabel('True positive rate')
    plt.title('ROC curve')
    plt.legend(loc='best')
    plt.show()

#Searching best alpha
print "Searching alpha to max Global Accuracy:"
acc = 0; best_acc = 0; alfa_max = 0;
alfas = np.arange(0.1, 1.0, 0.1)
for alfa in alfas:
    gnb = MultinomialNB(alpha=alfa, fit_prior=True, class_prior=None)
    for i in range(n_classes):
        y_pred[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])] = gnb.fit(X_train.toarray(), y_train[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])]).predict(X_test.toarray())    
    acc = global_accuracy(y_pred, y_test)
    if acc > best_acc:
        best_acc = acc
        alfa_max = alfa
print "Best alpha: " + str(alfa_max)
print "Best Global-Acc: " + str(best_acc)

def show_results(y_test, y_pred, y_pred_proba, n_examples=10):
    for example in range(n_examples):
        not_predicted = []
        example_index = y_test.index[example]
        print "Assunto: " + str(emails["assunto"][example_index])
        print emails["mensagem"][example_index]
        print "\n\n*********************************"
        print "*********** Predicted ***********"
        print "*********************************"
        for i in range(n_classes):
            if y_pred[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])][example_index] == 1:
                print str(emails.columns.values[i+3]),
                if y_test[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])][example_index] == 1:
                    print "(Correct)\n",
                else:
                    print "(Incorrect)\n",
            else:
                if y_test[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])][example_index] == 1:
                    not_predicted.append(str(emails.columns.values[i+3]))      
        print "*********************************\n"
        print "*********************************"
        print "********* Not Predicted *********"
        print "*********************************"
        for not_p in not_predicted:
            print not_p + "\n",
        print "*********************************\n"
        print "*********************************"
        print "********* Probabilities *********"
        print "*********************************"
        probs = dict()
        for i in range(n_classes):
            probs[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])] = 1.0 - y_pred_proba[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])][example_index]
            #print str(emails.columns.values[i+3]),
            #print 1.0 - y_pred_proba[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])][example_index]
        probs_ = sorted(probs, key=probs.__getitem__, reverse=True)
        for p in probs_:
            print p,
            print "%0.6f" % probs[p] 
        print "*********************************\n\n"

def at_least_n_pred(n, y_pred, y_test, y_pred_proba):
    for point in range(y_pred.shape[0]):
        index = y_test.index[point]
        #print "index: ", index
        #print "Soma: ", sum(y_pred.loc[index, class_names[:-6]]) 
        if sum(y_pred.loc[index, class_names]) == 0:
            #print "Será arrumado: ", index
            probs = dict()
            for i in range(n_classes):
                probs[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])] = 1.0 - y_pred_proba[str(emails.columns.values[i+3])][index]
            probs_ = sorted(probs, key=probs.__getitem__, reverse=True)
            #print "Prevsao sera em: ", probs_[0]
            for i in range(n):
                y_pred[probs_[i]][index] = 1

emails["n_words"] = emails.apply(lambda x : len(x["clean_message"].split()), axis=1)
emails["n_words2"] = emails.apply(lambda x : pow(x["n_words"], 2), axis=1)
emails["question_marks"] = emails.apply(lambda x : len(re.findall(r'\?', x["mensagem"])), axis=1)
